// Cortex-M3 + 64 KB SRAM / 512 KB flash, plus a RAM-mapped bxCAN register window for
// the thin-seam CAN driver content-gate. The gate asserts the exact register effects
// the DRIVER writes — MCR.INRQ init request, the BTR bit-timing value, the TX-mailbox
// TI0R/TDT0R/TDL0R/TDH0R load + TXRQ, the RX-FIFO RFOM0 release — and the Kani-proven
// config-only-in-init property (BTR written in Init, rejected+unchanged in Normal), on
// a plain memory region, deterministic, no dependence on Renode's CAN peripheral model.
cpu: CPU.CortexM @ sysbus
    cpuType: "cortex-m3"
    nvic: nvic
nvic: IRQControllers.NVIC @ sysbus 0xE000E000
    -> cpu@0
flash: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x0
    size: 0x80000
sram: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x20000000
    size: 0x10000
// bxCAN register window (real STM32F1 CAN1 address, 0x40006400, +0x400) as plain
// memory — driver MCR/MSR/TSR/RF0R/BTR/TIxR writes read back. Ends at 0x40006800,
// well below USART1 at 0x40013800 (no overlap).
can1: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x40006400
    size: 0x400
usart1: UART.STM32_UART @ sysbus <0x40013800, +0x100>
    -> nvic@37
